== THE SAN FRANCISCO FACTOID ==
Essential local trivia you'll probably forget almost immediately

In 1849 a number of ships were abandoned in the marshy cove of Yerba
Buena by crews who had caught "gold fever". In response to the shortage
of building materials and the need to find accommodation for a quickly
expanding population, pontoons were built out to these ships, which were
refurbished and converted into shops, restaurants, and hotels.


