== THE DAILY WORD ==
It's almost like learning something

kvass \'kvas\ also kvas - noun [Russ kvas] (ca. 1553)
1) A slightly alcoholic beverage of eastern Europe made from fermented
mixed cereals and often flavored
2) Thin, weak Russian beer

Usage example: "I find if I bathe in a huge vat of vodka-infused kvass
for a couple hours then rub myself with some of the CIA's stash of
imported illegal Beluga caviar, Putin finds me irresistible and will let
me 'mount his top-secret defense initiative,' if you know what I mean,"
giggled Lynne Cheney, to her bestest friend Limpy, a dead and
taxidermied iguana.


